dline for pre paying for tickets  or canceling and receiving a refund  is 1 August 2015  COL Jeff Boobar  Superintendent s Liaison to the Parents Council  is the coordinator for this event and he can be contacted for additional information at  540  464 7072 or BoobarJR vmi edu    Don t forget  Mail  calls  etc  Mail from home is the most important gift a cadet can receive  Be sure to get your new cadet s box number issued during the Matriculation process in Cameron Hall An occasional box of favorite foods from home also does wonders for a cadet s morale  Please do not send cash through the mail  The quickest way to contact a cadet is to leave a message at the VMI Visitor Center  540  464 7306 or send an email after classes start  Check Cashing The Cashier s office  located in Smith Hall  cashes checks up to  200  There are two ATM machines  BB T  located on post  one in Lejeune Hall PX area and the other is located in the Daniels  Courtyard  behind Shell Hall  VMI Bookstore   Lejeune Hall New cadets will make several purchases in the bookstore during Cadre Week and these purchases have to be paid for at the time of sale by cash  check  or major credit card  Matriculation Photos View photos of Matriculation and other events online with the option of purchasing them online at the VMI Photo store  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 